    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in RLC PDU encoder bit manipulation\n\n### Summary\nThe RLC PDU encoder in the NR stack had a critical bug in the `put_bit` function where it didn't initialize each byte to zero before starting to encode bits into it. This caused incorrect encoding when the buffer contained garbage data, leading to corrupted PDU headers.\n\nAdditionally, both the encoder and decoder initialization functions lacked proper parameter validation, which could cause crashes when called with NULL buffers or invalid sizes.\n\nThis fix addresses these issues by:\n1. Initializing each byte to 0 before encoding bits in the encoder's `put_bit` function\n2. Adding NULL checks and size validation to both decoder and encoder initialization functions\n3. Improving boundary checks in the encoder\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_rlc/nr_rlc_pdu.c`: Fixed encoder bit manipulation logic and added parameter validation\n\nWhen processing RLC PDUs with the NR RLC stack, users may observe corrupted PDU headers or unexpected behavior during encoding. In some cases, this could lead to incorrect RLC segmentation or reassembly failures. The issue is particularly noticeable when the PDU buffer contains uninitialized memory or when the same buffer is reused multiple times without proper clearing.\n"
}